ents demonstrate that our algorithms for solving the robust\noptimization problems are practical and can outperform state-of-the-art\nsimulation-based algorithms in the context of widely-studied stochastic optimal\nstopping problems from high-dimensional option pricing.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 4 Mar 2021 20:16:41 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 1 Jul 2022 01:29:41 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 16 Feb 2023 20:12:00 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 20 Mar 2023 13:44:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-21"}
